PART C: THE Q_1/ΣQ UNIVERSAL — PARETO DISTRIBUTION?
========================================================================
Q_1/ΣQ convergence (dominant mode fraction):
  p=   5: Q_1/ΣQ = 0.872678
  p=  31: Q_1/ΣQ = 0.812109
  p=  67: Q_1/ΣQ = 0.810899
  p= 103: Q_1/ΣQ = 0.810709
  p= 149: Q_1/ΣQ = 0.810636
  p= 191: Q_1/ΣQ = 0.810610

  Extrapolated limit: Q_1/ΣQ → 0.810607

The continuous limit: as p→∞, Q_k → Q(t) where t = k/p ∈ (0, 1/2)
  Q(t) = (sin(πt·(p-1)/2) / sin(πt))²

This is the FEJÉR KERNEL F_m(t) = (sin(mπt)/sin(πt))²!

The Fejér kernel is fundamental in Fourier analysis:
  - F_m(0) = m² (peak)
  - F_m(k/(2m+1)) = 0 (zeros at Chebyshev nodes)
  - ∫₀¹ F_m(t) dt = m (normalization)

So ΣQ_k ≈ m · p/2 = m²... let's check.

Sum of Q_k vs m² and m(m+1)/2:
